00:23:06.000 --> 00:23:12.000
And that is when I update the number of items, nothing is changing in this visualization down here.

00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:21.000
Only the chart that is affected by this input number of items in the code, you know, this input numeric is updated.

00:23:21.000 --> 00:23:27.000
And this is really important because imagine you had a visualization that takes like a minute to update and render.

00:23:27.000 --> 00:23:32.000
Well, what if you change any times you updated one of these numbers, you had to reload the whole application,

00:23:32.000 --> 00:23:35.000
which is how some frameworks work like it just would take forever.

00:23:35.000 --> 00:23:44.000
So it's super nice that inputs are defined in such a way that when you update something, only the components that use that input are re rendered.

