00:33:39.000 --> 00:33:43.000
Imagine you had some sort of app that was running in real time.

00:33:43.000 --> 00:33:46.000
And every like one second, it had to collect some new data.

00:33:46.000 --> 00:33:52.000
And I wanted to display a real-time stream of the values of this data.

00:33:52.000 --> 00:33:54.000
Invalidate later is super helpful for this.

00:33:54.000 --> 00:34:01.000
It basically tells this render.text function in this situation, in this example, that every 0.5 seconds,

00:34:01.000 --> 00:34:06.000
